    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="elec">
        <title>DIAGNOSTIC PROCEDURES FOR THE ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEM</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Sensor and Actuator Diagnostic Inspection</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The symbols &#60; &#38; > &#38;
                        <emph type="underscr">></emph>
                        are used in each of the diagnostic sections. They are defined as follows:
                    </para>
                    <para>(&#60;) indicates a
                        <emph type="underscr">value less than</emph>
                    </para>
                    <para>(>) indicates a
                        <emph type="underscr">value greater than</emph>
                    </para>
                    <para>(
                        <emph type="underscr">></emph>) indicates a
                        <emph type="underscr">value equal to or greater than</emph>
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Disconnect the harness connector from the sensor or actuator and inspect for corrosion, bent pins,
                spread terminals, or any condition that could cause an intermittent connection. Pin grip of the female
                terminal can be tested by inserting the appropriate tool from the terminal test adapter kit (ZTSE4435).
                Terminals that do not grip the sensor pins properly should be replaced, .
            </para>
            <figure id="f17503008" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figEg8/EG8831.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Testing Pin Grip</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
